Package: dbd-mysql-pm
Version: 2.1021
Revision: 1
Description: Perl5 Database Interface to MySQL
Type: perl
License: Artistic
Maintainer: Christian Schaffner <chris01@users.sourceforge.net>

# Dependencies:
Depends: mysql, dbi-pm, data-showtable-pm
BuildDepends: mysql-dev, libxml2, readline (>= 4.3-5), dlcompat-dev

# Unpack Phase:
Source: mirror:cpan:modules/by-module/DBD/DBD-mysql-%v.tar.gz
Source-MD5: 4a3e307502a746130d2f0d68d89247f5

# Compile Phase:
CompileScript: <<
  perl Makefile.PL PREFIX=%p INSTALLPRIVLIB=%p/lib/perl5 INSTALLARCHLIB=%p/lib/perl5/darwin INSTALLSITELIB=%p/lib/perl5 INSTALLSITEARCH=%p/lib/perl5/darwin INSTALLMAN1DIR=%p/share/man/man1 INSTALLMAN3DIR=%p/share/man/man3
  make
<<

# Install Phase:
UpdatePOD: true
DocFiles: README MANIFEST INSTALL.html ChangeLog
InstallScript: <<
  make install INSTALLPRIVLIB=%i/lib/perl5 INSTALLARCHLIB=%i/lib/perl5/darwin INSTALLSITELIB=%i/lib/perl5 INSTALLSITEARCH=%i/lib/perl5/darwin INSTALLMAN1DIR=%i/share/man/man1 INSTALLMAN3DIR=%i/share/man/man3
  mkdir -p %i/share/doc/%n
  ln -s %p/lib/perl5/darwin/DBD/mysql.pod %i/share/doc/%n
<<
DescDetail: <<
 DBD::mysql is an interface between the Perl programming 
 language and the mysql programming API that come with the 
 mysql relational database management systems. Most 
 functions provided by the programming API are supported.
 Some rarely used functions are missing, mainly because noone 
 ever requested them. :-)
<<
DescPort: <<
I couldn't use the default CompileScript since 'make test' normally
wouldn't pass: it needs a running mysql server with the necessary
test databases set up correctly.
<<
